caption: Really can’t go wrong here! Both their breakfast and lunch food is amazing
Food was fantastic. Atmosphere was great and the staff was generous and attentive. This place does not have much parking so I recommend car pooling if need be.
I was looking for a new place to try and was recommended this restaurant. Service was fast and friendly. Staff was attentive. Bonus points for being black-owned!
Friendly staff

30 years ago I used to frequent the steam table Frances' at Arlington and Clark, but I could no longer handle those portion sizes anyway. The Corn beef Ruben was superb, and the half I took home was fabulous the next day. The onion rings were perfect and a worthwhile indulgence. I will definitely return once I start eating in restaurants again.

Great! Three of us shared everything at brunch: a French toast flight, egg scramble with potatoes, and a Rueben.  This was the perfect amount of food; no one was too full, but we were all satisfied. Everything was fantastic.  I am not normally a French toast person but it was the standout of the meal.
The food was amazing. Hot, fresh and delicious

I am on a journey seeking out the most delicious sandwiches, and just came across at least one winner!! I had one of the new specials at Frances’ Deli! Smoked Pastrami on challah: I went with the traditional route, Swiss cheese and kraut. Every bite was it’s own Foodgasm!! Be back soon for other variations, and a picture before I finish!!! Yum!

Tasty menu, friendly staff, great location~  I went to breakfast on a Friday morning with a friend and we ordered based on the waitstaff's recommendation. The portions are massive, the staff is very familiar with the menu, and the food tastes great. The restaurant is wheelchair accessible both inside and outdoors. I recommend this restaurant for a morning breakfast or brunch. Took off one star because the coffee/espresso drinks are abnormally large and not made with correct proportions.
Their food is tasty but definitely overpriced. Loved the idea of the waffle flight though.
Food was excellent but it didn't seem like they sanitized the tables between guests.
Excellent food! Great customer service!
Great Brunch, Lunch, and Drink spot.  This place has been around for years and there's reasons for that.  Good quality food, good service, fun, and some nice updates on menu/decor.  Highly Recommend.

Very negative experience with management because of an error on the restaurants behalf through UberEats. I received the wrong order. Called the restaurant to speak with a manager and before I could finish explaining what was going on she finished my sentence rudely saying, “yeah I know another ‘Rachael’ ordered through UberEats so she has your food and you have hers.” This managers tone sounded like she could care less about their mistake and that if I wanted a refund I needed to contact Uber and if I wanted my correct order I needed to go back and reorder through the app. She took no responsibility for the mistake  and basically said I need to go about fixing their error. Very poor customer service. I also work in the industry and know that the restaurant has the option to refund the Guest via the UberEats tablet.  Is there a private  email where I can respond ?

Reasonable prices, good quality food and great coffee! Yes, try their coffee. It also has a very nice and positive atmosphere. I am taking one point off since the wait-time could be 1 hour! In reality, it is 5/5 if you don’t care about waiting time. In summary, my friends and I visited this place and we all were happy about the service, price and also food quality. I am not a huge fan of pancakes, but I really liked what I got from here. Give it a try ...
Adorable. lovely for a brunch with friends or a cute date. the food is fantastic and the employees are so nice. also the bathrooms are nongendered!!!

I've been to this restaurant plenty times but my last three visits here has been very disappointing. The food and the service was horrible. The only reason i gave it 3 stars is because on my last visit (yesterday) I didn't have to wait long to be seated. Don't plan on going back anytime soon. I really wanted to have my birthday brunch here but will definitely be looking for someplace else.

Although the service was very good and accommodating the place goes for shock over quality. I ordered the executive steak and eggs and tried the banana nut waffles. The steak was okay but was a bit overcooked for a med rare steak. The onions were raw instead of caramelized and the eggs were a bit watery. The food itself had real potential but seemed generally undercooked in everything. We were one of the first orders however. I would like too see if later in the day when the grill is warmed up if it improves the food.
The food is terrific and the service is even better!

This was the first brunch I ever had in Chicago and is still one of my favorite spots! I love the laid back, non-fussy atmosphere, and the menu has all of the classic brunch staples. They're usually a little busy and overwhelmed on the weekends, so just make sure you're not in any sort of rush.

We have been going to this restaurant for two years now as it is conveniently round the corner from where we live. The food has always been ok but slightly overpriced. We often would get frustrated with the poor service we would receive when visiting. However, since reopening after lockdown, I felt compelled to give a review. The food portions and quality have substantially dropped, and feels very overpriced for what you get! Not impressed and unlikely to visit again. I have given it two stars because the french toast flight is good!
Great service.  Good food and nice variety. Outdoor seating.   No GF bread options.
First time here today!! And I enjoyed every bit!! Everybody was friendly, our waitress was the best!! Food was amazing!! Can’t wait to return!!!
Chef is very creative. It was truly a visual and culinary delight. Some of the best food I have ever had in Chicago.. awesome.
Breakfast was delicious, but Costly.

Ordered the Blueberry Crunch French Toast, Grilled Potatoes, and a Veggie Omelette. For drinks a small Orange Juice and a Hibiscus Mimosa. Everything was great and the waitress Sophary was great too 👍🏽. The weather barely wanted to cooperate, but a little rain didnt kill me.
Amazing apple french toast! -@chicagobyob
Delicious breakfast sandwich (I got the breakfast wrap with chicken sausage). The sauce was amazing - just the right amount of kick and spice!

Save yourself the bother and... don't bother. This places features such highlights as... shells in the eggs, soggy bread, slow service and overpriced to boot!  Hey Frances, do yourself a favour and lose your celebrity chef (doesn't do much besides lounge at the bar anyway) and hire a proper cook!
Great service. Delicious food!!!
Lots of variety. Good deals good service.
My 1st time here and it was a great experience!! The service and food was very good. I told my bestie the next time she's back in town we will have to come back.
A mimosa flight is the way to go!
everything was delicious, the prices are fair and pretty good service
Delicious and unique takes on the classic American breakfast fare. Busy but fast service. One word: sumptuous.
Awesome choice of mimosas and filling food
We have dined here many times even during their transition....always excellent.
This place is 100% quality - there food is great and service is the best - pancakes are on point - menu is creative - had a genuine good time and meal there
Lovely vibe and amazing food!
Creative tasty menu! Service is good as well
Very good place and great service

This is a beautiful and delightful establishment. I went here with my sister for our birthday and I was so amazed. The food selection, preparation, quality is worth the wait. When I walked in I looked and felt like a kid in a candy store. My sister was surprised and delighted ( her face said it all) and that’s a hard task to achieve. I went for the French toast (OMG) and ended up leaving with the deli sandwiches ( turkey, corned beef and pastrami). This place is so good,  we came back the very next day got waffles and took more deli sandwiches for later on. The mimosas... Whoowee!! This place is clean...the bathroom, the floors even the corners of the tables. The food tastes fresh and doesn’t have the commercial undertones in taste. The waitstaff and service was as if I’d walked into someone’s home. Everyone was personable, down to earth. I wIll be visiting this establishment again very soon!!! I would especially like to thank the Chef for making both our birthday’s a most memorable one.  IMG_2641.JPG
Been my favorite since 1982 when it was across the street this place is awesome like the staff met my 1st love there
Great brunch

We had a business meeting here today and I must say I love this restaurant.  The food is great, the staff is friendly, and the ambiance is lovely (check out their Christmas Decorations I'm all about ambiance).  This is a Chicago restaurant that you must try...

OmGOSH!!! Questioning myself how it took me so long for my first experience at Frances’ Deli!!! I brought my friends from out of town here this past Sunday for brunch. All three of us were very pleased. The food was so yummy, staff so friendly, positive energy and vibes flowing and decor was warm, welcoming, super cute and comfortableI. After brunch I chatted with the owner about hosting my upcoming birthday brunch here... Everyone knows how important birthday brunch is!!! Needless to say, this is a great joint I will be recommending from here on out.

I grew up in Chicago, and every time I go back home there are certain restaurants that I have to visit.  A friend took me to Frances' the day after I had went to Manny's for my routine pastrami and latke. It took some convincing, but I ordered Frances' pastrami Rueben along with one of their latkes.  As much as I love Manny's, I must say that both the pastrami and latkes were far better here.  Can't wait to return for a breakfast and/or brunch
The selection, the food,  the service... all excellent. This will be a regular for us.

A good neighborhood spot with a welcoming atmosphere. Food was very good. The deli sandwiches were far above average and a pleasant surprise for someone who knows deli. Potato pancakes were also good but needed a little onion. Have a complete breakfast menu for the next time I go

Overall: After 6 years between visits, I can happily recommend the new and improved Frances'.  The good: 6 years ago the menu was strictly diner, which was fine but also lacked any variety or healthy options. Sometimes that's what you look for, but I was glad to be overwhelmed with options this time around. There's something for everyone, no matter what they're in the mood for. The waffle was large, fluffy, and packed with flavor thanks to the blueberry compote on top of it. There's also a ton more seating, and we didn't have to wait even though we had a party of 5 on a Sunday.  The not-so-good: The service was iffy at times and took a little longer than was expected, as was our wait for the food. The prices can also climb quickly if you're not careful, and the new atmosphere will certainly be cliche and tacky for some.  Food/drink: 8/10 Atmosphere: 8/10 Service: 8/10
Delicious food. Great atmosphere. I just wish the seats weren't so close together.

Most restaurants coast through breakfast....little thought, seasoning or creativity. This place is crowded on the weekends, but worth the wait. Attentive, friendly, knowledgeable service... Innovative breakfast menu...Can tell a trained chef runs this restaurant. Tasty from pastries to shrimp & grits.  They are known for very interesting approaches to french toast and waffles. Try the specials here....they are imaginative & you can not go wrong.
Awesome brunch. Five egg omelette.  Yes, five !

What has happened to Frances Deli? Ever since they remodeled it has gone down hill drastically. Was there for brunch yesterday. The food was awful and pricey. The supposed has browns were just a pile of mush that did not even resemble hash browns and $4 for regular coffee?? The clincher was after sitting there for 50 minutes we were asked to pay our bill and basically get out because they were so busy and wanted our table.Never going back.

Frances' was remodeled this year, and it has a completely different vibe than the Frances' of old. The good news is that the restaurant has been cleaned and polished. The menu is also shorter, simpler, and classier. It's still elbow-to-elbow for weekend brunch.  On the down side, it's gotten a little pricey. We were surprised at the cost of our meal.

This place is amazing!!! The food was absolutely delicious, and the service was superb. Our waitress even came ta get me after she brought our food to the table, because I was off taking pictures.  There can be a wait here, but tables also turn over fairly quickly, and the host(ess) will get yer number ta text you, so you can wander around the neighborhood if you like, instead of waiting there. We went and got coffee at Colectivo, which is just a few doors down.  The place is decorated in a fun, eclectic, whimsical way. If puts one in mind of a restaurant one might find in the French Quarter. It's bright & well lit so even though the tables are quite close together, it doesn't feel cramped. That being said, if one suffers from claustrophobia, this may not be the best place fer you, unless you can get a booth. The tables are VERY close together. The place is also loud, but not in that, "I can't have a conversation here!" way, there are just a lot of conversations, hustle & bustle, & folks enjoying the delicious offerings of the place.  This was definitely one of those places that has me very much wanting to come back, as there were so many items on the menu that I still wasn't to try, and the prices are quite reasonable. They have specials as well, so there is always something new ta try. This is a highly recommended experience!!!
Absolutely love this place. The best breakfast food to get in Chicago. Great service. Amazing decorations.

This was my first time here and my husband and I loved it. We will definitely come back. He had Cluck and Gaufre (I hope I spelled it right lol) which he liked very much. I had Corned beef skillet and it was very tasty but I wish it had had more corned beef. The french toast flight was delicious. The service was friendly and the place was very clean and cozy.

Ordered the chicken and waffles. Personally, I wasn't a fan of the flavor combination in their unusual sweet potato waffle, but the quality was definitely there.  More importantly, the food was definitely on the expensive side for what you get. I was a little surprised that you needed to pay extra to get toast or hash browns with the egg dishes, especially considering the initial prices.
The food here is divine.
Really good brunch! Worth the wait! I loved my egg sandwich!!
Wonderful food and experience!!!  Fish and chips was a bases loaded grand slam. Would have taken a picture  but nothing left ...as well as being stuffed to the gills.
I had the falafel something I can't remember the name but OMG was it amazing! I went back a week later. Such a great place for brunch.
Side of loaded hashbrowns = uncooked potatoes sprinkled with bacon & zero sour cream for $5+. Also barely warm.

The food was absolutely amazing!!!!!! Very friendly staff, comfortable atmosphere. Hard to decide what to eat with such an awsome menu!!!! Chef Rylon is with out a doubt the best chef in city!!!!!  Highly recommend you get here now!!! ✔✔
The food is great I had the chicken and waffles and it was awesome the place is a must go..👍🏽👍🏽
The food was delicious I had the jerk chicken Alfredo omelette it’s a must try all the foods looks so good and taste even better

Food was good, but service overall was just ok. I was greeted by a host/server and was seated, but asked to be reseated at different table. Server really had a poor attitude when I asked! A different server then took care of my table for some reason she was very pleasant. Will definitely try this place again and hopefully a better experience.
I appreciate places like this, everything was good from the hostess to the food. Definitely be coming back again and again

Delicious brunch that has great traditional breakfast foods and a surprisingly amazing Reuben sandwich. Check out the French toast flight and the mimosa flight, or the lox platter, which has very generous portions.
Great atmosphere and great service. I just wish they had more vegan menu items like pancakes, tofu scramble, and non dairy milk for coffee.
The only thing that had an actual flavor was the biscuits and gravy but it was awesome
Great food, and even better service, super large portions.
I thought we will find French breakfast food and we didn't...besides that, food is awesome

Hostess: 0/5 Food: 3/5 Service: 2/5 Management: 1/5  The hostess was very rude to our party, telling two members of our group to “go wait outside” after our quoted 20 minute wait extended to 45 minutes and after they went to check with her. Then, when we noticed her set up our table outside (knew it was ours by the number of seats and the high chair) we walked over to it (we had not sat down and only walked over after it had been set up for 5 or so minutes without a text or notification from the hostess) she walked by and said “well since you made yourselves at home...then go ahead.”  Our server was a little better (definitely not openly rude)...but not very attentive. My wife’s sandwich came out missing almost half of the listed ingredients. Just chicken, tomato, lettuce, and a bun. No garlic aioli, no grilled vegetables. My chicken and waffles were okay. Definitely the smallest chicken breast I’ve had served in a chicken and waffle dish. The sweet potato waffle was actually very good.  To top it off, the chef (who’s picture is prominently displayed outside on a street sign) was more concerned with SITTING at the table next to us loudly scolding (what I can only assume was a family member) about only tipping his server $1 last time he ate there after his meal had apparently been comped. I overheard him say something to the effect of “You know you never have to bring your wallet when you come to one of my restaurants...but you have to tip the staff.” This conversation lasted at least 20 minutes. This was in between the other times he was standing out front shooting the breeze with what appeared to be several different groups of personal friends who were eating at the restaurant. He was still sitting at the table when we left.  He wasn’t walking around checking on tables, clearly wasn’t in the kitchen making sure food came out with all the proper ingredients, or supervising his hostess who was rude to our group and several others we overheard.  We only stayed for our meal because the wait at several nearby brunch restaurants was 30+ minutes. However, I’m certain we will not be back.
Frances was good
Great menu, great staff.  First time eating here and will return.
I love this chef! I will follow him anywhere & I'm thrilled he has his own space! Everything is phenomenal!
Great Breakfast food all day, Mimosa flight 🤗🤗🤗
Food is so as well as the service.

I used to love Frances’ but this last visit was terrible. Super skimpy pastrami sandwiches, terribly slow service. I had to wait 20 minutes to pay my bill and could never catch the server for any service. I wanted to grab the bill as soon as she checked in on us—that never happened. I’m really disappointed in this experience.

Stumbled up Frances’ last week with my 2.5 year old son. I got the BLAT breakfast sandwich....maybe the best breakfast sandwich I’ve ever had. My son got the chocolate chip pancakes, any 2 year old’s dream. The staff was incredibly friendly. All around great experience. Can’t wait to go back.
It has delicious dishes and good service. Even though It was crowded, I sat within 10 min BTW, I highly recommend the lemon French toast; it's unusual flavor, but good.
Always good food and great service.
Table service was amazing and all of the food(Especially the bacon flight) was great

The food was good! Service however was slow. This is a good spot if you have time and aren't in a hurry, a leisurely brunch. Probably not great for a quick bite, as it took 10 mins to get a refill on coffee(even though the place was only about half full) and the woman who sat down next to us did not see a server for 20 mins. I'll go back again for the food, and hope the service will be a bit smoother.

Great location, friendly and fast service and excellent food. The Jerk Chicken Alfredo Omlette and the Chicken Fried Chicken were delicious. Didn't have it, but the Mimosa Flight looked amazing. Next time

Not my first time here since I live pretty close. But I guess ever since they changed ownership things are pretty bad over there. They dont know how to handle when its busy. The guy at the front was very rude and seat people that came after us before us. When I came and kindly mention that we were here before he had this fake smile and said that there are more people and that's why they took them first....we were waiting for 25 min...and they were seated as they walked it...not cool. Then he kept smiling and kept being annoying and rude... when I asked to speak to a manager he kept smiling and pretending like he is calling the manager. The manager was at the kitchen and didn't even pay attention to all the mess that was going on as we were not the only one with that issue...the food was not that great either and it took them a while also to get to us. To seat people that just arrived after people are waiting there for more than 25 min....bad for business. Won't recommend going there and won't go back.
Cold, loud and terrible service. Stay away

Oh. My. Gosh. Best french toast I've ever tasted in my life! They offer flights of french toast, pancakes, and mimosas. (The table next to us got the mimosas and we were seriously jealous). My friend got the Alfredo omlette and said it was great. Everything here looks amazing; we kept oogling the food of everyone around us. Plus it's decorated nicely and the staff is friendly. Can't wait to come back and try more of the menu!
We got bloody Mary's, the waffle flight, and lobster eggs Benedict. It was the single best brunch I've ever had, honestly can't recommend coming her enough. If you're in Chicago it's a must hit.
It had been a while since we visited last, but I was happy to see the good food is still there!
Great brunch - wide selection with generous portions

I've walked by this place for years on the weekend and never stopped until recently.. Their waffle options were amazing. Tried a few of them and I couldn't decide by favorite. They also have more savory breakfast options if you aren't in the mood for sweet. Coffee is also Dark matter and Divine.  Second visit: corned beef hash skillet was great. Chef came out and talked with us and a few other patrons. Great atmosphere. Great staff. Great food.
Keep it trashy, Frances!

The atmosphere during brunch rush is excessively loud as there doesn't seem to be any sound absorption. You need to yell to talk with people at your table.  Food was delicious, serving staff was efficient and checks are dealt with on a hand held terminal while your server stands, watching you tip. Slightly awkward
Heard the chef from Batter and Berries worked there.  The dish I like did not taste the same. I like the mimosa flight.
Hard to beat

IN LOVE with this place! The service was outstanding. The food was to die for. My friend got the mimosa flight, which I recommend. Also, not sure if it was the manager but he convinced us easily to stay and get another drink special as we were walking out. If I’m ever in Chicago again it will be one of the first places I visit!
Great food but prices a bit higher than similar brunch spots in the area
You can tell the food is made with love! Delicious!
Great updates

First time there! You gata ask for "Alexandra The Great"(server)! Her expertise and knowledge rittled with class was shown throughout our dining experience! Great food and atmosphere. Sincerely, Roderick.
Food was decent. Kind of long wait time to get food. Place is Kinda pricey.
Got the Mimosa flight, with the bacon flight, must have combo for brunch! For how full the place was, there was only a 30 min wait! Would recommend for brunch.

Came in to Frances on a Saturday at 11:30 am expecting a long wait, but was seated in 15 minutes to enjoy a great brunch! The menu is full of enticing options with a full page of breakfast and a full page of lunch. Paired with a mimosa flight of 4 full size mimosas for $18, this place can’t be beat! Oh and the aesthetic is made for IG!

BEST French Toast in Chicago. 👍👍 Nice crisp edges, no syrup needed! Excellent portion & quality for your $$. (no microwaves in here)  One and Only FRIED MATZO with ONION & SALAMI in Chicago?!?   Veni, vidi, vici   😉  🥇 My First.  A little bit hearty, but it's a great alternative to the boring omelette. Serves 2.  Seeing DARK MATTER coffee served in a deli style setup is amusing. 😁  ❤️❣️❤️  STRAWBERRY MIMOSA. I shall get a pitcher next time. 🥂  FRANCES DELI is still here, alive & well. 🤗  Have you seen the mega sandwich plates?  FULL. FILLED.  Can you see the salad plate? (See Video) ⛰️  I shall be back for more, especially the EXECUTIVE RIBEYE STEAK & EGGS (another value for your $$ moment). I'm definitely signing up for the Rewards Program.  Oh wait...I might as well move-in. 🤔  Say HI to my favorite gal pal, Nicola!  Frances is our bonding moment. Celebrate with US. Xoxo 😘😘
Chicken Avocado Club on sourdough, side of fruit and potato pancake

This is a very popular brunch spot so it gets crowded on the weekends! We went around noon on a sunday and had to wait 25 minutes to get seated. Their vegetarian skillet is delicious with a side of cheesy hashbrowns. I would recommend trying their french toast flight, it was amazing. They served us home made maple butter that was so subtle and tasty, it went perfectly with the french toast and maple syrup. They also gave us a bacon flight on the house which was pretty delicious according to my friends.
This was a great Sunday brunch spot! Highly recommend the mimosa flight and French toast flight.
Generous portions, crowded but great service. I imagine the deli part of the name is a legacy name. Great for breakfast,  brunch, and lunch.

Frances is fantastic! There are plenty of options for both lunch and breakfast for everyone’s eating preferences. I had the tuna melt and it was amazing. The portions were very big and all of the sandwiches come with delicious sides like the potato pancake. We will absolutely be back here!

Tasty brunch and drinks. Nice lively atmosphere and music. The manager even noticed that I was missing a condiment (that I hadn't even paid attention to) - and made sure to get me some of the spicy honey to go with my chicken and waffles.
Good place for breakfast or brunch.
Great service, inventive menu options. We will definitely be coming back!
Everything here is great. The potatoe pancakes are some of my favorite, the lox platter is massive
Great food!
Great local spot. Always busy. Breakfast food is the specialty of the house.
Probably the best waffle I've ever had.
Ask about the Bacon Flight! It's not on the menu and you will NOT regret it! We had fabulous service and a delicious, reasonably priced meal!

This was my first time visiting here and I absolutely loved it. Chef Rylon’s creations are unmatched. The service was amazing and the food is to live for!!! They also have the cheapest mimosa flight in town! I love all of the quotes on the wall. It gives the restaurant good energy. I will definitely be visiting again real soon! I have already made a few referrals that have visited the restaurant themselves and was happy that I made the recommendation! Five stars across the board!!
One of my favorite brunch spots in Chicago!

Great service and delicious food. The decor for the place fit very nicely and it's the perfect brunch spot. Drinks were great. Next time I'm definitely getting the mimosa flight. I was jealous of the table next to ours.

I was introduced to this gem last week! Super excited to be right back week two in a row! I love the decor, it’s bright and clean! You can tell someone put lots of thought into it right down to framing the city certifications on the wall. It’s very quaint and a bit intimate when packed but no worries because so far most patrons seem to be just as friendly as the staff! I guess it’s all the great vibes and energy from the decor and staff rubbing off on everyone! My first visit there Chef Rylon came out and talked with us, I love his energy and commitment very nice, personable, attentive guy! Parking is highly competitive find street parking and enjoy your stroll, you may not get a close park.  Food: to freaking die for! That’s all I got! No, but seriously the food is super bomb/fire/good af/delicious!!!  Mimosa flight is a must and very reasonably priced! May fave is peach and prickly pear. French toast flight is awesome! My fave is caramel apple and lemon! The maple butter I believe it is, is good enough to eat alone! Bacon flight was such a dope experience! I heart the duck bacon, flavorful and moist! Oh I have also had the jerk turkey patty- nothing more to say!!! Love the cheesy hash but eat quickly as they cool it gets hard/tough to work with. I did have the breakfast potatoes and so far I would say that’s the only thing which lacked pizazz/flavor. Spinach and mushroom omelet is classic with a good garlic/pesto sauce. Oh and  the executive ribeye is also very flavorful.

This was the first time @ Frances' Deli and Brunhery and  I thought the food was very good. I had the eye popping Robin of Locsley.  A great variety of vegetables along with locs. The Bloody Mary was outstanding also.
I love the flights of waffles. The service is excellent. The owner came to my table to ask how my meal was. My favorite restaurant in the area.
The service was very good and the menu has a variety of options. It's a local restaurant in my neighborhood and in my opinion worth visiting.

Went for my birthday, Got plain waffle with chicken and pancakes.   Really disappointed in the quality of the pancakes and waffles.  A mix would have been better.  Texture was gummy and hard for both.   Chicken was good.
If a picture is worth a thousand words, then let these photos speak for me. Chef Rylon is a culinary genius and I am delighted each time I dine at Frances'. Many happy returns...

Omg!!! Frances' is a must go! I visited on yesterday with friends and it did not disappoint in nooo way. The service was just as good as the food! We ordered the French toast flight, which is a must and large enough to share. Also, the Mimosa flight, my friends confirmed were impeccable (no cheap bubbles used)! Lastly, I ordered the pork chop executive...I can still taste it!!! My mouth is watering just writing this review. 😋  Why are you still reading this review?! Go...no run to Frances' now!!! Chef Rylon you have done it again...congratulations!🤗
Much cuter and more character inside than I expected. Mimosa flight is fun. Food is good. Friendly service.
Been here almost every Sunday since chef Derek Rylon took over, his creations are out of this world and delicious! Highly recommend, best brunch in Chicagoland area!
Delicious food, great service!
A wonderful brunch experience!
Delicious, adorable, friendly service. Good coffee!
Chef Royce whom created the batter and berry menu is here doing his thang! Food was delicious.
Great Food, Good Service, A bit Crowded but will return

Every time I come here it gets better and better. I get treated like a king and feel like a million bucks when I leave! This past time I ordered the lox platter (WOW). The presentation on this platter is incredible. I would quit my job and make it my life pursuit to be on the Bachelorette if I could only be presented a salmon rose from Frances' during the rose ceremony. This is a classic Chicago establishment with a modern twist. If you're in the Lincoln Park area do yourself and favor and take journey through their bountiful menu.
My Frances' Deli food was delicious!  The waiters and waitresses were very attentive with great customer service.
This place has great food. It's good for brunches and lunch! 100% recommend

I first went to Frances' a few months ago as I heard they had a good brunch menu. The food was absolutely amazing and very reasonably priced. One of the owners Chris came and asked how our experience was and I mentioned that it was great and this food would be really fun to do in our office. He took down my information and when I left expected nothing more. He then followed up the next day with a menu to cater to our office. I was very surprised and excited he would go out of his way to accommodate. The restaurant then catered our office for an event we had going on the following week and couldn't have been more pleased with the outcome. Not only does this place have amazing food but that experience alone solidified the type of people that work there. Great job to the team and thank you Chris for taking such care of us!!
It's the same guy from batter and berries!

Have not been here in a while, great fresh decor changes and food better than ever. Fresh fruit French Toasts and Waffles, truly amazing.The Chicken SweetPotato Waffle was the best waffle I have ever tasted. Went with a group of six and we all marveled at the different tastes and flavors, never before have I had a brunch extravaganza like this. The sandwiches are huge as well and traditional favorites with a twist. Service top notch as well. Must go when in Lincoln Park . Five Stars plus The drinks were also fabulous flavored mimosas and bloody Mary’s to die for

I love this place! France’s has great food and attentive service. I like that the chef adds new twists to old favorites, like the sweet potato waffle and fried chicken. This is a must place to go for breakfast, lunch, or a perfect weekend brunch.

love this place. biggest issue is the parking otherwise  spot on deli

Good! Huge menu. Like the updated decor and new owner, but lots of old favorites still on the menu.

Good breakfast place for Those with a sweet tooth, but they have the basics too. Lunch looked good and there were specials on tye board. Not the kind of old fashioned diner deli I remember bit good for an easy meal with wide appeal.
Get the Lincoln Park sandwich and cheese blintzes! Neighborhood go-to since I moved to Chicago 15+ yrs ago

This is my favorite breakfast spot! The new additions to the menu are outstanding and I love that they kept the neighborhood favorites as well.  The fresh interior updates made the  atmosphere feel cleaner and is refreshing. Frances was long overdue for some updates.  The staff is amazing. Service is impeccable.  Frances is my go to Brunch spot with family and friends.

Frances’ Deli used to be such a cool diner to go to. They had an awesome Reuben omelette that always kept me coming back. The interior of the place was classic and simple. Now, the place clearly caters to a trendier, less down-to-earth crowd. I couldn’t believe they painted over the coolest mural inside with hashtagbasic framed sayings like “Yes way rosé” and “Brunch without booze is just a sad, lonely breakfast”. They must’ve gotten that idea off of Pinterest. 🙄  The only reason I’m giving this place an extra star is because of my lovely waitress, who sympathized with my surprise at all the changes. She did a great job at recreating the Reuben omelette for me, and it wasn’t too bad. Ridiculously priced, but not bad. (Other one was definitely the best!)  The place should be renamed. No part of this restaurant is the same as the Frances’ from before. Be original in your new ownership rather than ride off of what once was. Painting over that mural was such a bad move, too. SUCH a silly move. Why did you do that?!

An excellent experience of a casual, neighborhood, American diner. I really love the ambience and mood of the restaurant, which seemed lively and engaging. The menu seems to have a full set of choices for breakfast, though their specialty still seems to be sandwiches and lunch. Our service was attentive and excellent. Eventually, the Chef stopped by to make sure that everything was OK. I enjoyed their sausage biscuit and gravy, though the gravy needed a little more sausage. We were able to find street parking, where we paid the meter, without too much trouble, early on a Saturday morning visit.
Great Restaurant with quality food , great staff and decent prices ;)
Had an amazing lunch today at Frances'... The food was great and the staff was even better!
Love this place! Tuna salad is the best in the city. I got the scallop omelet on special and it was honestly the best thing I've ever had for brunch.
Really enjoyed my breakfast - cheesey hash browns were amazing!

Just an awesome menu. Could eat breakfast and lunch daily for a month and get something different (I'd be obese from the generous portions but happy) that I'd love. Only negative and it's a small one is the Bloody was a weak mix, not bad but the culinary art they show in there food doesn't follow thru the Bloody.
I love the the old france's....new one look regular dinner place....
To go order incorrect. New ownership. Prices much higher.
Friendly staff.  Chef came out and told us specials.  Kid friendly.  Awesome brunch food.  Shared with friends and had artisan waffles, pancakes and also top notch biscuits and gravy!
Delicious! Every bite was amazing!
This place used to be the best on the block, new ownership seems confused on the branding and what to execute well. You can still get a similar skillet to before, but have lower expectations.
Excellent food!

Used to love this place. My favorite was the homemade sausage. When I asked about it, the new owner told me three times how bland it used to be, and I must be used to ‘plain flavor.’ Thanks for the insult, Derek. Won’t be coming back.

Frances' used to be one of my favorite breakfast places. It is now under new management and has a new menu. The quality of the food has gone downhill and the food is overpriced. I ordered an omelette and all the ingrediants were on top of the egg. The egg was also burned. Girlfriend ordered the breakfast wrap which has no flavor. It's so sad because I used to love this place but i won't be coming back.
Finally under new management. Very friendly. Great food!
Awesome service, even better French toast. This place is amazing for brunch
really disappointing changes to the menu. used to be delicious (BLAT sandwich), now their items are more expensive with poorer ingredients and subpar prep. sadly won't be coming back :(
Best breakfast/brunch I have found in the city. I can never pass on the Lou on the Lake sandwich, but am always tempted by the skillets.

New owners, new menu, increased prices and food quality has gone down the drain. I complained about my omelette and sausage patties and was told by the manager it's the same chef. It may very well be but the quality of the ingredients they are using has changed. The omelette's used to be fluffy, buttery and fulfilling: now they are just downright awful. They are clearly not using butter anymore but some cheap oil that burns the omelette and I simply will not return. So sad because it used to be a great diner.
New Chef, new menu and it's all great! The Chicken & waffles can't be missed, especially with that nutmeg hot sauce. Overall great neighborhood breakfast joint.

Gargantuan sandwiches. Get the triple decker if are aiming for deli heaven. Also, the best time for this place is their sidewalk seating during the summer. We brought the dog along to hang out, and he had a blast watching us and others enjoy lunch.

I have heard good things about the brunch here, but I chose to not have brunchy items the day I went. Instead I had the Cajun burger, of which I am now a fan. The meat was ell cooked and was moist and delicious. The fries that accompanied it were great as well.  They have some outdoor seating, inside it is much like a diner with a lot of wood, wodden walls, tables and chairs. They also have a vintage coke machine. I would say the service is a little slow, but I was with friends and was jabbering a lot, so I didn't really notice.  Go here if you want a solid brunch option.
Average breakfast. Average dinner.
Great food and service. Way more food than expected and they split the breakfast skillet in half for my girlfriend and I. would definitely come back.
Turkey reuben on sourdough, cheese blintzes, and chicken avocado club!
Amazing breakfast! Never crowded during the weekdays during the morning.
Great Jewish deli with fabulous matzo ball soup and great sandwiches at a reasonable price I'm looking forward to going back.
My FAVE deli on the Northside, real deal ChiTown chow and great staff. Weekend brunch is great too, try the Chocolate bacon pancakes!

Sandwiches and breakfasts are great! Shakes are AMAZING! Friendly staff. I don't recommend the fancy shwancy salad, but that just might be my preference.

One of the best deli's in Chicago (alongside The Bagel on Broadway).  Huge selection of food and the sandwiches are SO good.  If you've not tried Frances', you should -- for breakfast, lunch or dinner.

The habanero cheddar makes their omelette the best I've ever had. If only it were cheaper. At $1.50 per topping, they get expensive quick so it ends up being more of a special occasion omelette place as omelettes tend to run $15-16 each. Still, I find myself addicted. Francis ruined me.
My go to brunch spot. The reuben is amazing! Everything is so good. I've never had a bad experience there.

would give no stars. they don't have half the stuff on their menu. told my bf he could not have fries with his sandwich. i ordered half sandwich on onion roll, came on a bagel a the waitress tells me That's how they make them. then why are all these options mentioned on their menu? horrible place.
Try the Reuben omelette or the breakfast sliders. Although, everything is great!
A cute diner with a great brunch selection and prices.

This place serves brunch and lunch, but it's definitely all about the brunch food. Their pancakes are OUTSTANDING. I don't know what they put into them but those pancakes taste way too good to be healthy, LOL. Their omelettes are good, too. But where I have not had the best experience is with their lunches. The lunch food is tasty but overpriced for what they give you. My husband and I went there for lunch this past weekend and got two sandwiches and an iced tea. The sandwiches were regular-sized, by the way - it's not like they were gargantuan sandwiches. But the bill with tax and tip ended up being over $45. Are you kidding me? WAY too expensive for what we got. I'll be back ONLY for the pancakes and omelettes. Never again for lunch.

I'm always here digging into the cheap and plentiful breakfast specials including omelets and skillets. Plus, one time a departing brunch party gave us their side order of bacon completely free! That's like winning the brunch lottery. Expect to wait for your check a while during the brunch high times on weekends (11am-1:30pm) but the food comes out fast, and that's more important.
not a fancy place but great sandwiches and service.  very nice people. and community
Cool breakfast and brunch to have a delicious meal.   Service was good.  Most important the food was delicious!!

I like the place it was nice and family oriented. I had the skillet the potatoes were really good, cousin had the omelette with spinach, mushrooms and feta cheese...mmmhhh... It was good. I'm really going back to this place.

This place is amazing and I really enjoy the food and the service most definately one of my favorite eateries in Chicago

I crave their sandwiches every weekend! Love the #11 Lincoln Park (Turkey, Honeycup honey mustard and cheese on grilled challah) and the #15 Lou's on the Lake which is the same as #11 plus cranberry sauce, so good! Recommend getting the potato pancake and a milkshake to make any meal even better!  Wish they were open for weeknight dinners too!

I use to live down the street from this place and I would crave the challah french toast.  I prefer to go to this spot for brunch on the weekends, but be prepared to wait as it is a go to spot on Clark street for brunch.  I love the cookies and candy at the cashiers area.

The matzo and french toast challah are my favorites. The servers are friendly and good place for lunch or breakfast catch-up with friends.

Hard to go wrong with pretty much anything at Frances'  Breakfast or lunch options are abundant at fair prices.  Fairly ample street parking is available on Clark.  It does tend to get busy on the weekends and there really isn't a lot of space for people who are waiting to congregate so at some tables it can feel a little claustrophobic.  The potato pancake is out of this world and the number 11 sandwich is a must try.
Great fried egg sandwich.
